     REVISION HISTORY:
     =================
     
     BeamSolver  Version 1.0   (initial release)  June 16, 1995


     THE FUTURE:
     ===========

     BeamSolver may be considered somewhat limited due to the 
     relatively small number of solutions available, and the 
     lack of general solutions for the concentrated load cases.
    
     At present, there are a number of enhancements to BeamSolver
     as well as related projects that are being  considered, 
     however, there are no programming efforts in process at this 
     time. Any interest shown in BeamSolver refinements or any
     of the noted expansion projects will, no doubt, influence
     whether or not further development is initiated. 

     Registered users are entitled to receive the next major 
     update free of charge.


     BEAMSOLVER ENHANCEMENTS :
     =======================

         * Implement an easy to use Design by Criteria process.

         * "Grab and drag" using Mouse input routines to adjust
           the beam lengths, restraint locations, or location 
           of the applied load.

         * More beam configurations, and general solutions 
           provided for beams with concentrated loads.

         * Larger catalog of standard beam shapes/sizes.

         * Automatic superposition for multiple loading.
         
         * Print the output to a printer, a text file, or a
           image file.
           

     RELATED PROJECTS :
     ================

         * A program that calculates and evaluates local stresses 
           for trunnions and lugs attached to piping for pipe 
           restraint.

         * A program that performs analysis of local stresses for
           nozzle/shell connections per Welding Research Council
           Buletin 107.

         * A program that performs piping flexibility analysis
           for simple 3-plane geometry (Kellogg method)

         * Integration of Beamsolver and one or more of the above
           programs into one software package.
              
